      <tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>610 threads, <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=0>1</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=25>2</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=50>3</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=75>4</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=100>5</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=125>6</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=150>7</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=175>8</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=200>9</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=225>10</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=250>11</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=275>12</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=300>13</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=325>14</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=350>15</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=375>16</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=400>17</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=425>18</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=450>19</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=475>20</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=500>21</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=525>22</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=550>23</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=575>24</a> <a href=classes.html?class=9&start=600>25</a>  page(s) long</td><td  style='font-size: 9.5px;' align=right>&nbsp;<a href=classes.html?class=9&start=25>Next Page</a></td></tr></table></form><a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9>Root thread</a><table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9686963781757></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9686963781757><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>Shaman Guide Levels 1-9</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Sep 11th 2:19 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>&lt;center&gt;<br><br>&lt;font size=6&gt;&lt;u&gt;Guide to a Barbarian Shaman&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/font size&gt;<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;font size=4&gt;&lt;u&gt;Creation&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/fontsize&gt;<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;font size=3&gt;<br>Ok, my suggestion in this is to put 25 points into wisdom and put the other 5 into either intelligence or charisma, your choice.&nbsp;&nbsp;There is no choice of diety, and since this is a guide for Barbarian Shamans, there really isn't much else to say here.<br>&lt;font size=4&gt;&lt;u&gt;Level 1&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/fontsize&gt;<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;font size=3&gt;<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;spells&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;<br>Of coarse, like whenever you get spells, immediately scribe them.  You start out with Inner Fire and Minor healing, so go ahead and memorize them too.  Your level one spells, in order of most to least useful, are listed below, consequently, this is the order I suggest you buy them in.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Inner Fire-boosts hit points and armor class, as well as heals you better than minor healing, but takes more mana and time.  If you are in a hurry, use minor healing for healing, but if you have time, use this.  It's stackable, but it's AC(armor class) and HP(Hit Points) will not keep rising beyond the initial casting, it can be used to keep healing you though.  Always have this buff on.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Minor Healing-restores lost hp, doesn't work as well as Inner Fire, but it's faster and takes less mana.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Burst of Flame-DD(Direct Damage) once you get this, life gets much easier.  stand right at the entrance to the ramp, and cast it on 1 enemy.  He'll come hurtling toword you.  Back up untill he gets close enough to attack you, so you won't be in danger of being attacked by so many, and if you die, your corpse is right there, easy to find.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Strengthen-boosts strength.  Always have this buff on.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Dextrous Aura-boosts dexterity  Always have this buff on.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Flash of Light-blinds your enemies, not especially useful.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>True North-turns you North  Not as useful yet, but it will be.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Endure Cold-raises resistence to cold.  you won't be facing many spellcasters yet, and since you have naturally high cold resistence you should be okay.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Cure disease-cures disease.  Nothing should cast disease on you any time soon.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>K, youza got ya charachter.  You is da shaman, da wize man in a sea of fools.  Youza is the leader, the one in control, da one who passes judgement on da foolish rouges and da warriors.  Da other races is not so much your concern, but youza sometimes punish dem too.  You iz here to accomplish da will of six hammers, da tribunal.   Now, youza gonna deliver your guild letter.  Jus find da dock, and go left, da guild is datta way.  Seamus Finnigan, he good shaman, stand just outside.  Put on tunic, but save practice points, less you want to start makin ya own clothin, which wise.   Den youza goes back to da dock, swimses across, and goes past de zone into everfrost.  go down ramp, there be guards there, help ya when da skellies train and come ta kills ya.  At bottom o the ramp, there be fork.  Don't take it.  Stay there and kill the critters.  There be spiderlings, gnolly pupses, da rotten skellies, da white bear cubs, an da wolfies, an da ice gobbies....you no like them, cept kill.  Kill da gnollies and gobbies and skellies first level...but be careful, don't take fork, so can find corpse, and don't get mo dan one ons ya.  If dey train ons ya, run fors da guards, dey helps ya.  Gobbies an gnolls and skellies got good loot, so youza keeps any containors.   Dey got cash too.  Don attack skellies wit da weapons yet, dey kill ya.  Keepsa killin dem till ya gots to de next level.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;font size=4&gt;&lt;u&gt;Levels 2-4&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/fontsize&gt;<br>&lt;font size=3&gt;<br>Okay, once you reach Level 2, immediately go back to Halas.   First thing to do is to start buying spells.  Buy them in the order listed above (except of coarse Inner Fire and Minor Healing.)  Level two is quite easy, since you should have burst of flame and should hopefully be able to handle the creatures near the ramp...provided you only get one at a time.  Beware, though, con (right click or target and type c) every single ting, especially skellies.  If you see a vengeful composer, soloist, or lyracist, run!  They will kill you.  I garantee it.  At this level you should be able to take on Polar Bear cubs, spiderlings, and wolves.  Save ruined bear pelts, bear pelts, spiderling silk, ruined wolf pelts, and chunks of meat.  Sell everything else (except for containers, you should use those).    If you have enough money left over from buying your spells, then go ahead and buy a tailoring kit.  It will be very useful, and Halas/Everfrost is a tailorers paradise.   The polar bear skins (the ones that aren't ruined) you should give to the lady in Mac's Kilts.  She'll give you a piece of tattered armor, one gold, and some exp.  Some time during these levels, you should purchase a large Lantern, it'll be worth it, trust me.<br>&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;Tailoring&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;<br>Buy a tailoring kit, and you can make the following items from just the stuff in everfrost/Halas.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Tattered armor:Buy a pattern (sold by the lady in Mac's Kilts in Halas or the merchants just outside the zone change to everfrost, there's three of them standing near a fire) and combine it with a ruined bear or ruined wolf pelt.  If it works, then you get a piece of armor.  If you made it from the bear pelt then it will be large, and you can wear it.  If it was made from the wolf pelt, it's small and you can't wear it, but you can sell it for sevral gold.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Silk Thread:combine 2 spiderling silks.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Silk Bandages:combine 2 silk threads   You can use these for bandaging wounds if you want, but since you are a healer, it shouldn't be that important.  They up your tailoring skill quite a bit though.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;font size=4&gt;&lt;u&gt;Level 5&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/fontsize&gt;<br>&lt;font size=3&gt;<br>&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;spells&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/u&gt;<br>Gate-Takes you back to the guard station.  One of the best spells you get.  Very very very good.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Summon Spirit pouch-summons a containor that can hold 4 items.  Very useful, but you have to watch out, when you log out you lose them and anything in them.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Feet Like Cat-Ups your agility.  Always try to keep this buff on, even if it does take a lot of mana.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Sicken-DoT(damage over Time) spell.  Very useful, good for pulling creatures.  The only problem is that it has to be bought out on the plains.  It's a very very scary place.  Don't even try to go there, instead, try to get a high level shaman to go get it for you.  I didn't get it till level 8, so don't worry if you don't get it immediately.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Summon Drink-Summons water.  It will save you a few silver, which at this point is quite useful.  <br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Drowsy-Slow spell.  It will also get the baddies movin toward you, so very good to use for gettin them to attack you.   It's what you should use if you can't get sicken.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Fleeting Fury-This spell boosts you stats for about 12 seconds.  It's not really that useful, unless your grouped with a tank, in which case it lets him pack in a little more damage for a while.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Scale Skin-Boosts AC.  You can't use this spell untill you have snake scales, which is why it's so far down on the list.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Frost Rift-DD.  It's not that useful in the northlands, since most creatures have a resistance to cold.  Useful when you leave though.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Endure Fire-Raises Fire Resistance.  You don't really need it yet.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Cure Poison-Cures poison.  Nothing should be poisoning you yet.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Keep on like you've been doing for the past  4 levels, and beware, if you lose your corpse, you start out with nothing now, so you really need to be careful.  Keep tailoring, it will definetely help you.  You might even want to purchase a fishing pole and some bait, it's a good way to get food cheap.  With Fishing and summon drink, you should rarely have to buy food.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;font size=4&gt;&lt;u&gt;Level 6&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/fontsize&gt;<br>&lt;font size=3&gt;<br>Okay, here is where it gets a bit tough.  If the creatures around there still con blue, your in luck, keep killin em.  If, however, like me, they conn green, then you need to set off for Black Burrow.   Make sure you have a full set of tattered armor before you go.  Group with one or two other L.6 or so people, and set off for the ramp to BB(Black Burrow).  To get there, take the fork left, and keep going that way untill it forks again.  You'll immediately see 2 forks, but if you look carefully, to the right there is a narrow path full of snow banks.  It's kind of hard to see.  Go that way, and you should find an igloo.  If you want you can camp (this is different for camping as in logging off.  It means to sit and wait for creatures to spawn.) here and kill the ice goblin whelps and scouts, which should be blue to you.  If your getting impatient, then keep going.  At the next fork, go left.  Fairly soon, you should see another fork, here you go right.  About ten steps later you'll find another fork, go left.  Keep going strait, and soon you should reach a large cave.  There will be two gnoll guards there.  (you are in a group, right?)  You and your group should just camp there and kill them, then go up the tunnel they are guarding a ways and kill the next scrawny gnoll guard, and then the next, and then the next.  Then return to kill the 2 guards, which should have spawned by now.  Keep doing this untill level 7, then, if they are green, go to BB, and if they are blue, you could either stay, or go on ahead to Black Burrow.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;font size=4&gt;&lt;u&gt;Level 7&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/fontsize&gt;<br>&lt;font size=3&gt;<br>When you enter Black Burrow, you'll be in a cavish area, where 3 scrawny gnolls spawn.  Try to hit one of them at a time with drowsy, and they should attack you.  Keep killing them untill L.8.  Watch out though, do not, under any circumstances let one run away into they lower levels.  They'll go down and recruit about 15 other gnolls to help them kill you.  It's not a good thing.  You should be near the zone line, so if your in trouble, run.  Remember, by Level 7,  you shouldn't be afraid to group and go do stuff.   You don't have to stick exactly to this guide.  This is just a steady, easy way to reach L.9....when things get fun.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;font size=4&gt;&lt;u&gt;Level 8&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/fontsize&gt;<br>&lt;font size=3&gt;<br>If you want, you can keep killing more gnolls, by now you should be taking on the gnolls, the scrawnys should usually con green.  You might want to go to Queynos.  You get meditate at this level though, so before you do anything else, gate home and train a point in the skill meditate.  Here, just do whatever you want.  The world is open to you now.   Queynos hills is also a good place to hunt, or, if your daring, you can group and go hunting on the plains, but watch out, the creatures there vary greatly in level, so try and stay near the guards, and always, always, always keep enough mana for gate.<br>&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;Tailoring, again.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/u&gt;<br>If you go out to hunt on the plains, try to kill the spiders.  Loot their spider silk, and you can use it to make silk armor.<br>Silk Swatch:two spider silks<br>Silk Armor:one silk armor and a pattern for all except leggings and tunics, which take two silk swatches and a pattern.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;font size=4&gt;&lt;u&gt;Level 9&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/fontsize&gt;<br>&lt;font size=3&gt;<br>Okay, here is where you change from newbie to an actual player, at least it is for the shaman.  L.9 is a milestone in your career, and it is definetely something to look forward to.<br>&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;Spells&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/u&gt;<br>Spirit of Wolf(sow)-haste.  Really Really Really useful spell.  Buy it immediately.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Serpent Sight-infravision!  Finally, you can ditch the lantern and actually see.  You have to get an enchanter to buy it for you at the enchantors guild.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Light Healing-A better Healing spell!  YAY!<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Summon Food-summons food  No more having to buy food.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Tainted Breath-DoT spell, much better than sicken.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Spirit of Bear-Stamina Buff<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Sense Animals-Sense nearby Animals<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Spirit Sight-see invisable<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Cure Blindness-cures Blindness<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Endure Disease-raises disease resistence.<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>&lt;p&gt;<br>Here I leave you.  It's time for you to figure it out yourself!  Have fun.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
